Package org.ulpgc.edp.model.dct

Class Dictionary

java.lang.Object
org.ulpgc.edp.model.dct.Dictionary
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Object>
public class Dictionary extends Object implements Iterable<Object>
Class which represents a dictionary data structure. It stores pairs of key - value on an efficient way. Accessing an element is almost O(1).
  • Javier Castilla - Principal and leader developer of the class.
  • David Miranda - Special contribution in put method development.
  • Esteban Trujillo - Special contribution in basic pop method development.
  • Elena Artiles - Special contribution in basic clear method development.
Author:
Javier Castilla, David Miranda, Esteban Trujillo, Elena Artiles

  • Constructor Details

    • Dictionary

      public Dictionary()
      Constructor by default. Initializes an empty dictionary.

    • Dictionary

      public Dictionary(Iterable<?> items)
      Constructor given an iterable of pairs key - value as tuples to put into the new dictionary. Length of tuples must be 2, nor more neither less. The same result as initializing an empty dictionary and calling update(Iterable) later.
      Parameters:
      items - to put into the new dictionary
      Throws:
      TypeError - if element of tuple is unhashable
      ValueError - if a container with size different from 2 is found

    • Dictionary

      public Dictionary(Object... items)
      Constructor given some arguments dynamically. The number of arguments must be even. This is necessary because the first element will be the key and the second one its value. The same result as initializing an empty dictionary and calling update(Object...) later.
      Throws:
      TypeError - if some key element is unhashable
      ValueError - if number of arguments is not even

    • Dictionary

      public Dictionary(Dictionary dictionary)
      Constructor used to create a copy of a dictionary. The same result as initializing an empty dictionary and calling update(Dictionary) later.
      Parameters:
      dictionary - to take items from

    • union

      public static Dictionary union(Dictionary dict1, Dictionary dict2)
      Calculate the union of two given dictionary items sets. The order of insertion in the result dictionary will be given by the order that the parameters are given. If keys sets are the same, dict2 take priority over dict1.
      Parameters:
      dict1 - to make union
      dict2 - to make union
      Returns:
      a new dictionary result of the union of other two

    • put

      public void put(Object key, Object value)
      Inserts a pair key - value into the dictionary. If the key is already into the dictionary items set, its value will be replaced with the given one. If it is needed to avoid this updating, use setDefault(Object) or setDefault(Object, Object) instead. No mutable object is allowed as key, otherwise, an exception will be thrown. Non accepted key objects are: Collection Map Arrays Dictionary
      Parameters:
      key - to store or update
      value - associated to the key
      Throws:
      TypeError - if key is unhashable

    • del

      public void del(Object key)
      Removes the pair key - value associated to the given key. Non element is returned when deleted. If it is needed to know if the element was deleted, use pop(Object) or pop(Object, Object) instead.
      Parameters:
      key - to delete
      Throws:
      KeyError - if the dictionary does not contain the given key

    • pop

      public Object pop(Object key)
      Removes and returns the pair key - value associated to the given key. If an exception is needed to be avoided, use pop(Object, Object).
      Parameters:
      key - to remove
      Returns:
      the value of the removed pair key - value
      Throws:
      KeyError - if the dictionary does not contain the given key

    • pop

      public Object pop(Object key, Object defaultValue)
      Removes the pair key - value with the given key. If the key is not into the dictionary, a default value will be returned.
      Parameters:
      key - to remove from the dictionary
      defaultValue - to return if the key is not contained
      Returns:
      the value of the removed pair key - value

    • get

      public Object get(Object key)
      Searches and returns the value paired with the given key. This method could lead to ambiguity if some of the inserted values were done as null. If not nullity of values could not be defended, use get(Object, Object) instead.
      Parameters:
      key - to search its value
      Returns:
      the value in pair with the given key if contained else null

    • setDefault

      public Object setDefault(Object key)
      Returns the value paired with the key if exists, else adds the given pair key - value to the dictionary and returns that value. Value will be default as null. If it is needed a certain default value, use setDefault(Object, Object) instead.
      Parameters:
      key - to search or add
      Returns:
      the value found or added

    • update

      public void update(Object... items)
      Updates the current dictionary with the elements given dynamically. Note that the number of given arguments must be even. This is needed because the first element will be the key associated to the second one, and so on.
      Parameters:
      items - to insert into the dictionary
      Throws:
      ValueError - if number of arguments is not even

    • update

      public void update(Iterable<?> items)
      Updates the current dictionary with all the elements given by the iterable. Elements into iterable must be sets of length 2, nor mores neither less. If the iterable returns an element that cannot be converted to a sequence an exception will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      items - to iterate and take key - value from
      Throws:
      TypeError - if some element cannot be converted to a sequence
      ValueError - if some element has length different of 2
